    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If your shell supports it, would something like this work ? </p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>javac com/**/*.java \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If your shell does not support <code>**</code>, then maybe</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>javac com/*/*/*.java\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>works (for all packages with 3 components - adapt for more or less).</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 277416,
      "reputation" : 694244,
      "user_id" : 571407,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2f0d9dec16bae1e06552af55ddefc11f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "JB Nizet",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/571407/jb-nizet"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1310121149,
    "creation_date" : 1310121149,
    "answer_id" : 6623222,
    "question_id" : 6623161,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I would advice you to learn using <a href=\"http://ant.apache.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">ant</a>, which is very-well suited for this task and is very easy to grasp and well documented.</p>\n\n<p>You would just have to define a target like this in the build.xml file:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;target name=\"compile\"&gt;\n    &lt;javac srcdir=\"your/source/directory\"\n           destdir=\"your/output/directory\"\n           classpath=\"xyz.jar\" /&gt;\n&lt;/target&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
