    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1428087142,
    "creation_date" : 1428087142,
    "answer_id" : 29438033,
    "question_id" : 6623161,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I'm just using make with a simple makefile that looks like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>JAVAC = javac -Xlint:unchecked\nsources = $(shell find . -type f -name '*.java')\nclasses = $(sources:.java=.class)\n\nall : $(classes)\n\nclean :\n        rm -f $(classes)\n\n%.class : %.java\n        $(JAVAC) $&lt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It compiles the sources one at a time and only recompiles if necessary.</p>\n"
